'''Borhane Abro''', (born 1995) is a Djiboutian swimmer.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bcn2013.com/en/swimming/detail/member/borhane-ahmed-mohamed-abro |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130812112155/http://www.bcn2013.com/en/swimming/detail/member/borhane-ahmed-mohamed-abro |archivedate=2013-08-12 |df= }}</ref> He competed in the [[2012 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) – Men's 50 metre freestyle|50]], [[2012 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) – Men's 100 metre freestyle|100 m freestyle]], [[2012 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) – Men's 50 metre butterfly|50 m butterfly]] and [[2012 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m) – Men's 100 metre butterfly|100 m butterfly]] events at the [[2012 FINA World Swimming Championships (25 m)]]. Borhane also took part in the [[Swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships – Men's 50 metre freestyle|50 m freestyle]] and [[Swimming at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships – Men's 50 metre butterfly|50 m butterfly events]] at the [[2013 World Aquatics Championships]].

