{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=July 2017}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Dori Lal Agarawal Sports Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Dori Lal Agarawal Sports Stadium | former names = Regional Sports Stadium | location = [[Bareilly]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1960 | built = | opened = 1998 (First cricket match recorded) | renovated = 2015 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]] | operator = [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/57917.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''Dori Lal Agarawal Sports Stadium''' or '''Regional Sports Stadium''' is a multi-purpose stadium in [[Bareilly]], [[Uttar Pradesh]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket, and other sports. The stadium was established in 1960 and has hosted international matches<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/912_misc.html Other Match]</ref> between [[India women's cricket team]] and [[Sri Lanka women's cricket team]].<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/158/158469.html India women vs. Sri Lanka women]</ref>
In 2015, the [[Government of Uttar Pradesh]] decided to upgrade the stadium's core via construction of a dormitory with 400 beds for both male and female players, as well as staircases.<ref> [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bareilly/Sports-stadium-set-for-up-gradation/articleshow/45875266.cms Sports stadium set for up gradation]</ref><ref> [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bareilly/2-new-stadiums-to-come-up-in-Bareilly-villages/articleshow/46459356.cms 2 new stadiums to come up in Bareilly villages]</ref>
In August 2015, the stadium hosted the Indian Gramin Cricket League, a local [[Twenty20]] tournament for rural areas.<ref> [http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/bareilly/Dorilal-stadium-gets-facelift-for-rural-T-20-tournament/articleshow/48701961.cms Dorilal stadium gets facelift for rural T-20 tournament]</ref>
