{{one source|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Stade Pierre Claver Divounguy | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = Port Gentil | coordinates = {{coord|-0.725749|8.783414|display=inline,title|type:landmark}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | tenants = }}
The '''Stade Pierre Claver Divounguy''' is a stadium primarily used for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches in [[Port-Gentil]], [[Gabon]]. It is the home of the Gabonese team [[AS Stade Mandji]] of the [[Gabon Championnat National D1]]. The stadium has capacity to 7,000 people.
==External links== *[http://www.worldstadiums.com/africa/countries/gabon.shtml Venue information]
