{{Orphan|date=February 2013}}

<!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:Tblade full kit.jpg|200px|right|]] -->
''T-Blades'' are a type of hockey skate blade manufactured by the German company T-Blade {{Interlanguage link multi|GmbH|de|3=Gesellschaft mit beschränkter Haftung (Deutschland)}}. Unlike tradition skate blades, T-blades are replaced when worn out. The manufacturer of the T-Blade states that "Compared to conventional skate blades, the T-Blade runner lasts 4-5 times longer." The T-Blade is held to the skate chassis by a stabilizer and six screws which require a special three-pronged wrench. The blades are sold pre-sharpened. [[Jochen Hecht]] of the [[Buffalo Sabres]], [[Dennis Seidenberg]] of the [[New York Islanders]], [[Marcel Goc]] of the [[Nashville Predators]], and [[Christian Ehrhoff]] of the [[Buffalo Sabres]]<ref>{{cite news|last=Elfin|first=David|title=On-ice safety is secondary: despite improvements in equipment, players aren't exactly safety-conscious|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-86233303.html|newspaper=Insight on the News|date=May 13, 2002}}</ref> are NHL players who use T-Blade skates.{{Citation needed|date=January 2013}}

