{{Icehockey-stub}}

This '''timeline''' lists the foundation dates of the national governing bodies for '''[[rugby union]]'''&mdash;known as rugby unions or federations. The first union was the [[Rugby Football Union]] (RFU) that was founded in 1871 to govern rugby union within [[England]]. It was founded following the first ever rugby union international, played between [[England national rugby union team|England]] and [[Scotland national rugby union team|Scotland]] in 1871. The [[Scottish Rugby Union|Scottish Football Union]] (later renamed the Scottish Rugby Union) was then founded in 1873, the [[Irish Rugby Football Union]] in 1879 and the [[Welsh Rugby Union]] in 1881.
==Timeline== *1871 (English) [[Rugby Football Union]] (RFU) *1873 [[Scottish Rugby Union]] (as Scottish Football Union until 1924) *1879 [[Irish Rugby Football Union]] (a merger of two Irish unions both formed in 1874) *1881 [[Welsh Rugby Union]] *1889 [[South African Rugby Board]] (merged with South African Rugby Union in 1992 to form South African Rugby Football Union; merged body renamed South African Rugby Union in 2005) *1892 [[New Zealand Rugby]] (founded as New Zealand Rugby Football Union, known as New Zealand Rugby Union from 2006–2013) *1895 [[Zimbabwe Rugby Union|Rhodesia Rugby Football Union]] (Zimbabwe RU after 1980)<ref name="Zimbabwe">{{cite web|url=http://www.zimsevensrugby.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=93&Itemid=50 |title=THE HISTORY OF ZIMBABWE RUGBY |publisher=zimsevensrugby.com |accessdate=2007-12-13}}</ref> *1899 [[Argentine Rugby Union]]<ref name="Argentina">{{cite web| url=http://www.uar.com.ar/union_momentos.htm |title=HECHOS SALIENTES DE LA HISTORIA DEL RUGBY INTERNACIONAL Y NACIONAL |publisher=uar.com.ar |accessdate=2007-12-13 |language=Spanish |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20071210211528/http://www.uar.com.ar/union_momentos.htm |archivedate = 2007-12-10}}</ref> *1900 [[Deutscher Rugby-Verband|German Rugby Federation]] *1908 [[Sri Lanka Rugby Football Union]] (as Ceylon Rugby Football Union)<ref name="Ceylon">{{cite web |url=http://www.srilankarugby.com/rugby_history.html |title=A 100 years of Unbroken Tradition! |publisher=srilankarugby.com |accessdate=2009-06-06 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090606132335/http://www.srilankarugby.com/rugby_history.html |archivedate=2009-06-06 |df= }}</ref> *1913 [[Fiji Rugby Union]] (founded as Fiji Rugby Football Union) *1916 [[Royal Moroccan Rugby Federation]]<!-- <ref name=completerugby> --><ref>{{cite book | page = 71 | editor-last = Bath | editor-first = Richard | date = 1997 | title = Complete Book of Rugby | publisher = Seven Oaks Ltd | ISBN = 1-86200-013-1}}</ref> *1919 [[French Rugby Federation]] *1920 [[Guyana Rugby Football Union]]<ref>http://www.worldrugby.org/member-unions/61</ref> *1921 [[Malaysian Rugby Union]] (As Malaya Rugby Union)<!-- name=completerugby</ref>--><!--Bath, Richard (ed.) ''The Complete Book of Rugby'' (Seven Oaks Ltd, 1997 ISBN 1-86200-013-1) p71</ref> --><ref>{{cite book | page = 71 | editor-last = Bath | editor-first = Richard | date = 1997 | title = Complete Book of Rugby | publisher = Seven Oaks Ltd | ISBN = 1-86200-013-1}}</ref> *1922 Catalan Rugby Federation *1923 [[Spanish Rugby Federation]] *1923 [[Tonga Rugby Football Union]] *1923 [[Samoa Rugby Football Union]] *1923 [[Kenya Rugby Football Union]] (as Rugby Football Union of Kenya) *1926 [[Japan Rugby Football Union]] *1926 [[Portuguese Rugby Federation]] *1926 [[Czech Rugby Union]] (as Czechoslovakia) *1928 [[Italian Rugby Federation]] *1928 [[Trinidad and Tobago Rugby Football Union]] *1931 [[Romanian Rugby Federation]] *1932 [[Dutch Rugby Union]] *1932 [[Swedish Rugby Union]]<!--name=completerugby/> Bath, Richard (ed.) ''The Complete Book of Rugby'' (Seven Oaks Ltd, 1997 ISBN 1-86200-013-1) p75</ref> --><ref>{{cite book | page = 75 | editor-last = Bath | editor-first = Richard | date = 1997 | title = Complete Book of Rugby | publisher = Seven Oaks Ltd | ISBN = 1-86200-013-1}}</ref> *1934 [[Hellenic Rugby Federation]]<ref>http://www.worldrugby.org/member-unions/56</ref> *1935 [[Belgian Rugby Federation]] *1935 [[Chilean Rugby Federation]]<ref>http://www.feruchi.cl/index.php?id=35</ref> (as Rugby Union of Chile) *1936 [[Rugby Union of Russia]] (founded as, and successor of, Rugby Union of the Soviet Union) *1937 [[Thai Rugby Union]] *1946 [[Korean Rugby Union]]<!-- name=completerugby/> Bath, Richard (ed.) ''The Complete Book of Rugby'' (Seven Oaks Ltd, 1997 ISBN 1-86200-013-1) p70</ref> --><ref>{{cite book | page = 70 | editor-last = Bath | editor-first = Richard | date = 1997 | title = Complete Book of Rugby | publisher 